SUMMARY:Trans Rights and Bodily Autonomy - Robert’s Rules Training
DESCRIPTION:The Trans Rights and Bodily Autonomy Working Group is holding a training on Robert’s Rules of Order Newly Revised (RONR) as we work towards more structured meetings. \nThis is a great opportunity for members new and old to learn the essentials of RONR—the parliamentary procedure used across Seattle DSA. We’ll discuss how these rules specifically apply to working group meetings and have time for questions. \nOnce the training is over we’ll jump straight into our Biweekly Meeting where everyone can practice their parliamentary prowess If you’d like to attend\, please register for the regular meeting and arrive online on Signal by 7:30pm. \nAll DSA members are more than welcome to attend this training.
URL:https://seattledsa.org/event/trans-rights-and-bodily-autonomy-roberts-rules-training/
LOCATION:WA
CATEGORIES:Trans Rights and Bodily Autonomy Working Group
END:VEVENT
