SUMMARY:Solidarity Dinner: South Seattle
DESCRIPTION:Dinner for the people! \nHelp us cook\, serve\, eat together\, and connect with our neighbors. \nWe feed our community\, no questions asked\, because we believe in our world where no one goes hungry. \nSaturdays in South Seattle:\n-Cooking shift: 1:30-4pm in Tukwila\n-Serving shift: 4:30-7pm at Cafe Red (across the street from the light rail station) \nTo volunteer for a cooking or serving shift\, follow the instructions here. \nWe are also looking for financial supporters. It costs just $2 to feed a hungry neighbor. Support here!
URL:https://seattledsa.org/event/solidarity-dinner-south-seattle/2026-04-11/
LOCATION:Cafe Red\, 7148 Martin Luther King Jr Way S\, Seattle\, WA\, 98118\, United States
CATEGORIES:Mutual Aid,New Member Friendly
